<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-49-0088 </DOCNO><TEXT>Heligoland is an island in the North Sea which 65 km off shore occupies1.5 km/sup 2/ of the German Bay. The island's existing oil-fired cogeneration-typedual-purpose power plant is due for modernization. It will be replacedby a system allowing the generation of electric power and the supplyof district heat as well as the processing of drinking water. Renewableenergy sources, namely wind and oceanic heat, are planned to be minimizingthe island's primary energy consumption. The paper deals with the windpower plant, the cogeneration plant, and the flue gas purification system.</TEXT></DOC>